    "246 Moreover, by grounding its decisions in specific precedents, the AI model would also open itself up to scrutiny and challenge.",
    "If humans disagree with a particular decision, they could probe the applicability and appropriateness of the cited precedents, arguing that the current case is meaningfully different or that the precedents themselves were wrongly decided.",
